# Sprint 3: Revolutionary Component GUI System

**Duration:** 2 weeks  
**Sprint Goal:** Build the revolutionary component-driven GUI that will redefine psychological experimentation  
**Success Criteria:** Visual component composition, real-time editing, and GPU-accelerated experiment preview

---

## Revolutionary Sprint Objectives

1. **ComponentForge Visual Builder**: Revolutionary drag-and-drop component composition interface
2. **Component Library Browser**: Searchable, categorized component palette 
3. **Real-time Component Editor**: Live code editing with instant visual feedback
4. **GPU-Accelerated Preview**: WebGL2 experiment preview with <2ms timing
5. **Component Marketplace Foundation**: Architecture for community component sharing

---

## Revolutionary Sprint Backlog

### Epic: ComponentForge Visual Builder
**Story Points: 10**

#### GUI-REV-001: Component Canvas System
**Points: 6 | Priority: Critical**

**Description:** Build the revolutionary component canvas where users compose experiments visually by dragging and connecting components.

**Revolutionary Features:**
- GPU-accelerated component rendering with WebGL2
- Real-time component connections and data flow visualization
- Physics-based component interaction (snap, magnetism, collision)
- Multi-touch gesture support for component manipulation
- Infinite canvas with smooth zoom/pan (0.1x to 10x)
- Component hierarchy visualization with tree/graph views

**Technical Requirements:**
```typescript
// Revolutionary Component Canvas
interface ComponentCanvas {
  // GPU-accelerated rendering
  renderer: WebGL2Renderer;

  // Physics-based interactions
  physics: ComponentPhysicsEngine;

  // Real-time component system
  componentSystem: ComponentSystem;

  // Gesture recognition
  gestureHandler: GestureRecognitionSystem;

  // Performance monitoring
  performanceMonitor: CanvasPerformanceMonitor;
}

// Component manipulation with μs-precision
class ComponentManipulator {
  dragComponent(component: BaseComponent, startPos: Vector2, endPos: Vector2): void;
  connectComponents(source: BaseComponent, target: BaseComponent): void;
  animateTransition(component: BaseComponent, animation: ComponentAnimation): void;
}
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Component canvas renders at 144fps on target hardware
- [ ] Drag-and-drop operations complete within 2ms
- [ ] Component connections visualized with animated data flows
- [ ] Gesture recognition supports multi-touch manipulation
- [ ] Canvas scales smoothly from 0.1x to 10x zoom
- [ ] Component physics feel natural and responsive
- [ ] WebGL2 fallback to WebGL1/Canvas2D gracefully

**Revolutionary Canvas Architecture:**
```svelte
<!-- ComponentCanvas.svelte -->
<script lang="ts">
  import { onMount } from 'svelte';
  import { ComponentCanvas, WebGL2Renderer } from '$lib/canvas';
  import type { ComponentForge } from '@psyforge/forgescript';

  export let forge: ComponentForge;

  let canvasElement: HTMLCanvasElement;
  let canvas: ComponentCanvas;

  onMount(async () => {
    canvas = new ComponentCanvas(canvasElement, {
      enableGPUAcceleration: true,
      enablePhysics: true,
      targetFPS: 144,
      maxFrameTime: 2,
    });

    await canvas.initialize(forge);
  });

  function handleComponentDrop(event: ComponentDropEvent) {
    canvas.addComponent(event.component, event.position);
  }

  function handleComponentConnect(event: ComponentConnectEvent) {
    canvas.connectComponents(event.source, event.target);
  }
</script>

<canvas
  bind:this={canvasElement}
  class="component-canvas w-full h-full"
  on:componentdrop={handleComponentDrop}
  on:componentconnect={handleComponentConnect}
/>
```

---

#### GUI-REV-002: Component Library & Palette
**Points: 4 | Priority: Critical**

**Description:** Create the revolutionary component library browser with AI-powered search and instant preview.

**Revolutionary Features:**
- AI-powered component search and recommendations
- Live component preview with interactive demos
- Component performance metrics and compatibility indicators
- One-click component customization templates
- Community ratings and usage statistics
- Smart component suggestions based on experiment context

**Component Categories:**
```typescript
interface ComponentLibrary {
  // Display Components
  display: {
    text: TextComponent[];
    image: ImageComponent[];
    video: VideoComponent[];
    canvas: CanvasComponent[];
    chart: ChartComponent[];
    3d: ThreeDComponent[];
  };

  // Input Components  
  input: {
    keyboard: KeyboardComponent[];
    mouse: MouseComponent[];
    touch: TouchComponent[];
    voice: VoiceComponent[];
    eyetracker: EyeTrackerComponent[];
    biometric: BiometricComponent[];
  };

  // Layout Components
  layout: {
    grid: GridComponent[];
    stack: StackComponent[];
    circle: CircleComponent[];
    timeline: TimelineComponent[];
    spatial: SpatialComponent[];
  };

  // Animation Components
  animation: {
    motion: MotionComponent[];
    transition: TransitionComponent[];
    physics: PhysicsComponent[];
    particle: ParticleComponent[];
  };

  // Specialized Paradigms
  paradigms: {
    stroop: StroopComponent[];
    nback: NBackComponent[];
    iat: IATComponent[];
    visualsearch: VisualSearchComponent[];
    attentionalblink: AttentionalBlinkComponent[];
  };
}
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Component search returns relevant results in <100ms
- [ ] Live preview renders components without affecting main canvas
- [ ] Drag-and-drop from library to canvas works seamlessly
- [ ] Component filtering by performance/compatibility works
- [ ] AI suggestions adapt to current experiment context
- [ ] Component performance metrics display accurately

---

### Epic: Real-time Component Editor
**Story Points: 8**

#### GUI-REV-003: Live Code Editor with Component Integration
**Points: 5 | Priority: Critical**

**Description:** Revolutionary Monaco editor integration with real-time component highlighting and instant visual feedback.

**Revolutionary Features:**
- Real-time bidirectional sync between code and visual components
- Component IntelliSense with AI-powered completions
- Live type checking with ComponentForge API
- Instant error highlighting with suggested fixes
- Code execution preview without affecting main experiment
- Collaborative editing with operational transforms

**Monaco Enhancement:**
```typescript
// Revolutionary Monaco Integration
class ComponentMonacoEditor {
  private editor: monaco.editor.IStandaloneCodeEditor;
  private componentSync: ComponentCodeSync;
  private aiAssistant: CodeAIAssistant;

  setupComponentForgeAPI(): void {
    // Register ComponentForge TypeScript definitions
    monaco.languages.typescript.typescriptDefaults.addExtraLib(`
      declare module '@psyforge/forgescript' {
        export class ComponentForge {
          text(content: string): TextComponentBuilder;
          stimulus(content: string): StimulusBuilder;
          response(): ResponseBuilder;
          layout(): LayoutBuilder;
          trial(name?: string): TrialBuilder;
          experiment(title: string): ExperimentBuilder;
        }

        export interface TextComponentBuilder {
          fontSize(size: number): this;
          color(color: string): this;
          position(x: number, y: number): this;
          fadeIn(duration: number): this;
          typewriter(speed: number, cursor?: boolean): this;
          build(): TextComponent;
        }

        // ... comprehensive API definitions
      }
    `);
  }

  enableRealTimeSync(canvas: ComponentCanvas): void {
    this.editor.onDidChangeModelContent(() => {
      this.componentSync.updateVisualFromCode(
        this.editor.getValue(),
        canvas
      );
    });
  }

  enableAIAssistance(): void {
    this.aiAssistant.registerCompletionProvider();
    this.aiAssistant.registerHoverProvider();
    this.aiAssistant.registerCodeActionProvider();
  }
}
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] Code changes reflect in visual canvas within 50ms
- [ ] Component selection in canvas highlights corresponding code
- [ ] IntelliSense provides comprehensive ComponentForge completions
- [ ] Error diagnostics include component-specific guidance
- [ ] AI assistant suggests component improvements
- [ ] Collaborative editing maintains consistency

---

#### GUI-REV-004: Component Inspector & Property Editor
**Points: 3 | Priority: High**

**Description:** Advanced component property editor with live preview and performance optimization suggestions.

**Revolutionary Features:**
- Live property editing with instant visual feedback
- Performance impact indicators for property changes
- AI-powered property optimization suggestions
- Property animation timeline editor
- Bulk property editing across multiple components
- Property templates and presets system

**Property Editor Interface:**
```svelte
<!-- ComponentInspector.svelte -->
<script lang="ts">
  import type { BaseComponent } from '@psyforge/forgescript';

  export let selectedComponent: BaseComponent | null;

  $: properties = selectedComponent?.getEditableProperties() || [];

  function updateProperty(key: string, value: any) {
    if (selectedComponent) {
      selectedComponent.setProperty(key, value);
      // Trigger real-time update
      canvas.invalidateComponent(selectedComponent);
    }
  }

  function optimizeProperties() {
    if (selectedComponent) {
      const suggestions = ai.optimizeComponentProperties(selectedComponent);
      applyOptimizations(suggestions);
    }
  }
</script>

<div class="component-inspector">
  {#if selectedComponent}
    <h3>Component Properties</h3>

    {#each properties as property}
      <PropertyEditor
        {property}
        on:change={(e) => updateProperty(property.key, e.detail.value)}
      />
    {/each}

    <button on:click={optimizeProperties}>
      🤖 AI Optimize
    </button>
  {/if}
</div>
```

---

### Epic: GPU-Accelerated Preview System
**Story Points: 6**

#### GUI-REV-005: WebGL2 Experiment Preview
**Points: 4 | Priority: High**

**Description:** Revolutionary experiment preview system with GPU acceleration and real-time performance monitoring.

**Revolutionary Features:**
- WebGL2-accelerated component rendering
- Real-time performance profiling with <2ms guarantee
- Physics simulation for component interactions
- Multi-viewport preview (desktop/tablet/mobile)
- Time-travel debugging for experiment playback
- Automatic performance optimization suggestions

**WebGL2 Architecture:**
```typescript
class ExperimentPreviewRenderer {
  private gl: WebGL2RenderingContext;
  private componentRenderer: ComponentRenderer;
  private performanceProfiler: PerformanceProfiler;

  async initializeWebGL2(canvas: HTMLCanvasElement): Promise<void> {
    this.gl = canvas.getContext('webgl2')!;

    if (!this.gl) {
      throw new Error('WebGL2 not supported');
    }

    await this.setupShaders();
    await this.initializeBuffers();
    this.enablePerformanceMonitoring();
  }

  renderExperiment(experiment: Experiment): void {
    const frameStart = performance.now();

    this.gl.clear(this.gl.COLOR_BUFFER_BIT | this.gl.DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT);

    // Render all components with GPU acceleration
    for (const component of experiment.getAllComponents()) {
      this.componentRenderer.render(component);
    }

    const frameTime = performance.now() - frameStart;
    this.performanceProfiler.recordFrame(frameTime);

    if (frameTime > 2) {
      console.warn(`Frame time exceeded 2ms: ${frameTime.toFixed(3)}ms`);
    }
  }
}
```

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- [ ] WebGL2 rendering maintains 144fps consistently
- [ ] Frame times never exceed 2ms on target hardware
- [ ] Multi-viewport preview updates simultaneously
- [ ] Performance profiler provides actionable insights
- [ ] Automatic optimization suggestions improve performance
- [ ] Graceful fallback to Canvas2D when WebGL2 unavailable

---

#### GUI-REV-006: Real-time Performance Dashboard
**Points: 2 | Priority: Medium**

**Description:** Comprehensive performance monitoring dashboard for component and system optimization.

**Dashboard Metrics:**
- Frame time histogram with 2ms target line
- Component render time breakdown
- Memory usage tracking
- GPU utilization monitoring
- Input latency measurements
- Network performance for collaborative features

---

### Epic: Component Marketplace Foundation
**Story Points: 4**

#### GUI-REV-007: Component Sharing Architecture
**Points: 3 | Priority: Medium**

**Description:** Foundation for community component sharing and collaboration.

**Revolutionary Features:**
- Component packaging and versioning system
- Automated component testing and validation
- Component performance benchmarking
- Community ratings and reviews
- Dependency management for component libraries
- Hot-swappable component updates

---

#### GUI-REV-008: Community Integration
**Points: 1 | Priority: Low**

**Description:** Basic community features for component sharing and collaboration.

---

## Revolutionary Quality Gates

### Performance Requirements
- [ ] **Frame Rate**: Maintain 144fps on target hardware
- [ ] **Frame Time**: Never exceed 2ms per frame
- [ ] **Memory Usage**: <512MB for complex experiments
- [ ] **Startup Time**: Application interactive in <1 second
- [ ] **Component Response**: Visual feedback within 16ms of user action

### Technical Requirements
- [ ] **WebGL2 Support**: Full GPU acceleration with fallbacks
- [ ] **Component System**: All UI backed by ComponentForge
- [ ] **Real-time Sync**: Code ↔ Visual sync within 50ms
- [ ] **AI Integration**: Smart suggestions and optimizations
- [ ] **Collaborative**: Real-time multi-user editing

### User Experience Requirements
- [ ] **Intuitive**: New users create experiments in <5 minutes
- [ ] **Powerful**: Expert users have access to advanced features
- [ ] **Accessible**: WCAG 2.2 AA compliance maintained
- [ ] **Responsive**: Works on desktop, tablet, and large mobile
- [ ] **Reliable**: Zero data loss, robust error handling

---

## Revolutionary Audit Requirements

### AI Audits (MANDATORY for Sprint Advancement)

**Gemini Pro GUI/Architecture Audit:**
- [ ] Component architecture scalability and maintainability
- [ ] User experience flows and interaction design
- [ ] Performance optimization effectiveness
- [ ] Visual design system consistency
- [ ] Accessibility implementation comprehensiveness

**O3 Technical Implementation Audit:**
- [ ] WebGL2 rendering pipeline efficiency
- [ ] Real-time synchronization algorithm correctness
- [ ] Component system memory management
- [ ] Performance monitoring accuracy
- [ ] Error handling and edge case coverage

### Revolutionary Success Criteria
- [ ] Users can create a complete Stroop experiment visually in <2 minutes
- [ ] Code-visual synchronization is seamless and instant
- [ ] Performance never drops below target thresholds
- [ ] Component library provides comprehensive paradigm coverage
- [ ] AI suggestions demonstrably improve experiment quality

---

## Implementation Strategy

### Week 1: Foundation & Core Systems
- **Days 1-2**: ComponentCanvas WebGL2 foundation
- **Days 3-4**: Component Library browser
- **Days 5**: Monaco editor ComponentForge integration

### Week 2: Integration & Polish
- **Days 6-7**: Real-time code-visual synchronization
- **Days 8-9**: Performance optimization and monitoring
- **Days 10**: AI features and marketplace foundation

### Risk Mitigation
- **WebGL2 complexity**: Incremental implementation with fallbacks
- **Performance targets**: Continuous monitoring and optimization
- **Real-time sync**: Simple algorithms first, optimize later
- **AI integration**: Basic features first, enhance iteratively

---

## Revolutionary Impact

This sprint will deliver the world's first GPU-accelerated, component-driven psychology experiment builder. Users will be able to:

- **Compose experiments visually** with drag-and-drop components
- **See code changes instantly** in the visual preview
- **Get AI suggestions** for optimization and improvement  
- **Share components** with the community
- **Achieve impossible precision** with <2ms timing guarantees

**This sprint makes psychforge the most advanced experiment platform ever created.**

---

*Previous: [Sprint 2: Compiler](sprint2.md) | Next: [Sprint 4: Live Mirror-Canvas](sprint4.md)*

